metadata.title: Netlify
metadata.content:
Netlify
We provide a Netlify build plugin,
[netlify-plugin-inngest](https://www.npmjs.com/package/netlify-plugin-inngest)
, that allows you to automatically sync any found apps whenever your site is deployed to Netlify.

metadata.title: Netlify
metadata.content:
Netlify
Setup
1. Install `netlify-plugin-inngest` as a dev dependency:
Copy Copied
```
npm install --save-dev netlify-plugin-inngest
# or
yarn add --dev netlify-plugin-inngest
```
1. Create or edit a `netlify.toml` file at the root of your project with the following:
Copy Copied
```
[[plugins]]
package = "netlify-plugin-inngest"
```
Done! 🥳 Whenever your site is deployed, your app hosted at
```
/api/inngest
```
will be synced.

metadata.title: Netlify
metadata.content:
Netlify
Configuration
If you want to use a URL that isn't your "primary" Netlify domain, or your functions are served at a different path, provide either
```
host
```
,
```
path
```
, or both as inputs in the same file:
Copy Copied
```
[[plugins]]
package = "netlify-plugin-inngest"

[plugins.inputs]
host = "https://my-specific-domain.com"
path = "/api/inngest"
```
